Knowledge: learning and educating lessons of natural science, social studies and history (learning and educating the children with learning difficulties and intellectual disability). 
Skills: composing lesson material, analyzing lessons, changing the level of learning and lesson material.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Understand the teaching principles, methods and techniques of teaching children with learning difficulties and intellectual disabilities in natural and social sciences (natural science, social studies, history); learning and education planning and building of analytical skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student 1) is familiar with the principles and methods of teaching natural sciences and social subjects to children with special needs and are able to put the knowledge into a larger pedagogical context;  2) is able to use new practical and theoretical knowledge when planning lessons, teaching and analysis (including when choosing methods, activities and study materials as well as when determining the appropriate difficulty level)
